Wash and dry produce.

Trim and cut @scallions{2} into ½-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice into half-moons. Transfer cucumber to a #medium bowl{} and cover with @salt{}; toss to coat. Let sit ~{3-5%minutes}, then rinse and drain. Return drained cucumber to bowl.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and @salt{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallions; cook, stirring, until lightly charred, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%oz} and @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly softened and lightly browned, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Stir in @sesame seeds{1/2%tbsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if necessary. Turn off heat; transfer to a second medium bowl. Wipe out pan.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and stir in @bulgogi sauce{4%oz} and @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}. Simmer, stirring constantly, until mushrooms are coated and sauce has thickened, ~{1%minute}.

While mushrooms cook, add @gochujang sauce{1/2%oz}, @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, remaining @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and @korean chili flakes{1%tsp} to bowl with drained cucumber. Toss to coat.

> Add as many chili flakes as you like to adjust the spiciness.

Fluff rice with a fork.

Divide rice between bowls; top with cabbage stir-fry, saucy mushrooms, and cucumber pickles (draining first) in separate sections. Garnish with remaining @sesame seeds{1/2%tbsp} and serve.